comment:
“The face of a damn hippo.” 😂 

She’s delivers that line so resolutely, it’s priceless.
I love how despite being the villain, Fiona always has these small moments of human decency.

1:13 "I was a woman of my time." Delphine.
"That is a crock of shit! You've got a mean streak wider then your backside, or a sickness of the mind." Fiona sneered. "Either way, if TEN of the hundreds of things I have read about you are true? Then you deserved every minute down there, under all that dirt."
Kathy Bates is such a brilliant actress that I vehemently hate the character she is portraying, a true actress, she makes every character come alive.
"People have always celebrated the macabre. You're not remembered fondly, but I guess that beats not being remembered at all."
